We .. ummmm .. errr ... /em mumbles &quot;how do I say this?&quot;  .. oh yeah!<br>
We ... KICKED ASS!!! yeah thats what I mean!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I just wanted to thank everyone in attendance for the Hole Raid.  This was one of the smoothest raids I have ever tried running and it was all because of the people that were there.<br>
<br>
Those in attendance:<br>
<br>
Montag &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Raid leader<br>
Deloit &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Group leader &amp; Super-Nuker<br>
Asyth &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Group leader, Main Looter, and Fuzzy Companion<br>
Xenophon &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Main Tank,  Main Bazooka,  Heck .. Main Howitzer<br>
Mugo &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Master Mezzer <br>
Crelen &lt;Oblique&gt;  Helluva Healer<br>
Farrienka &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Debufftress 'espciale<br>
Shindara &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Speak Softly, Carry BIIIG Thumpin Stick<br>
Coddington &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Gnome with a Vengeance<br>
Morromid &lt;One Fellowship&gt; Bane of the Elemental<br>
Amiral &lt;One Fellowship&gt; Wizard with an Itchy Trigger Finger<br>
Tjohn &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Double Sword Ginsu Machine<br>
Sytox &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Mega Dots and Mana Battery<br>
Zenapwu &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Beasty BadAss<br>
Aladara &lt;Arrow of Light&gt; Shammy Extraordinare<br>
<br>
Complete raid Breakdown:<br>
<br>
Well things started off a little slow.  We didnt actually get into the Hole until 6:40 EST, But once we got the groups formed up everything was smoothe sailing from there.  <br>
<br>
Onward to the Castle.... Did a grat job of mopping up every MoB from the castle entrance to the City Entrance and it seemed like we were clearing out the Old homesteads in no time at all.   <br>
<br>
Gotta Stop and cash a Check....  Made our way to the Old bank and tried to get a Loan on a Bag for Mugo.  Unfortuanately his Credit must not have been the best becuase Polzin Mrid wouldnt let him have it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    No worries tho we will get him next time.<br>
<br>
Things slowed down a little here and we had a little trouble with  Some MoB Complete Healing.  After getting that straightened out though we began to set up for our charge deeper into the City.  A couple of people had to leave at this point as it was getting close to the Set raid time .. Thanks to Amiral and Shindara for all their help to get us as far as We did.  Took on a Couple named Mobs here and a BUNCH of thier friends.  Our group was rock-steady though and we took them all out no problems.  Great work by everyone on this,  talk about pulling through as a team.<br>
<br>
Say a litttle prayer for my baby...  Our final stop of the evening was just outside (what I think to be) the church.  We set up outside the main entrance and got ready to pull the inhabitants.  For some reson though they were reluctant to leave thier Sanctuary. (Gee i cant imagine why that would be /snicker)  Even after being Dotted, Debuffed, poked, prodded and called numerous names by our party they still didnt want to join our shin-dig.  However once they got over thier Shyness they decided to invite all, and i do mean ALL of thier friends.  Maybe they heard we had Summoned booze or something /shrug.<br>
<br>
 Ok I have to say this is one of the Finest Battles that i have ever had the pleasure of being involved with in EQ.  I lost track of the number of enemies that we had to destroy but they defintely outnumbered our entire party.  Wave after wave of elementals and imps poured out of the entryway and we knocked them down one by one .. this was at least a 20 minute long fight,  Casters were out of mana almost 3 times over,  my stamina bar was gone for more than half the battle im sure.  Yet eventually we prevailed, losing two of our number along the way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Sorry Coddington and Asyth.  Never let anyone say they did not fight the good fight.<br>
Once again you all were SUPERB.  Everyone kept their cool and did what needed to be done.  Truely one of the best performances i have ever seen by any fighting force.<br>
<br>
During the battle we dropped Tzitzi the Crazed and managed to get the final piece for my Karana Paladin helm.  Yay.  I wish that we could have done more and gotten some more drops for everyone, but never fear we will do this again soon enough and hopefully take down all the mobs we need to.   Since it was already over an hour past the scheduled raid time we decided to gate ourselves out and Split the loot.<br>
<br>
Once again my sincerest thanks to everyone who participated.  You made this a completey enjoyable experence.<br>
<br>
Yours in Service,<br>
Montag McCleaud<br>
Arrow of Light <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=montagmccleaud>Montag McCleaud</A> at: 3/2/03 3:37:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deloit>Deloit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Sleepy Time Express Guildie</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#000080>(3/2/03 5:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Post Raid Wrapup</span><hr size=1> Montag that was one of the most enjoyable raids i have ever been on (screw a dragon raid....this one was fun). That end fight (thank you for being there mugo and Crelen for keeping us alive so we could ironicly kill) was one of the best extended fights i have had in EQ so far. Thanks for keeping the spirits up during all that Montag.  <br>
